Matt.17.1","text":"And after six days Jesus taketh Peter, James, and John his brother, and bringeth them up into an high mountain apart,","year":32},{"id":"recMHAkpvwtEiXCLq","ref":"Matt.17.2","text":"And was transfigured before them: and his face did shine as the sun, and his raiment was white as the light.","year":32},{"id":"rectyiAyRbhUTys14","ref":"Matt.17.3","text":"And, behold, there appeared unto them Moses and Elias talking with him.","year":32},{"id":"rec0919fWxLJNT0FC","ref":"Matt.17.4","text":"Then answered Peter, and said unto Jesus, Lord, it is good for us to be here: if thou wilt, let us make here three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias.","year":32},{"id":"recxYiNskXZgSDFUC","ref":"Matt.17.5","text":"While he yet spake, behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them: and behold a voice out of the cloud, which said, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased; hear ye him.","year":32},{"id":"rec7lWImNPYnB9p99","ref":"Matt.17.6","text":"And when the disciples heard it, they fell on their face, and were sore afraid.","year":32},{"id":"recdKg0dTJV7wsryl","ref":"Matt.17.7","text":"And Jesus came and touched them, and said, Arise, and be not afraid.","year":32},{"id":"recYiPRWRi5PrbPJf","ref":"Matt.17.8","text":"And when they had lifted up their eyes, they saw no man, save Jesus only.","year":32}]}
